      "side": 0,
      "message": "Yes (well, assuming you run the next line, `emerge-...`). A non-cros-workon ebuild [1] will always pick up changes to itself on rebuild.\n\n(One caveat there is the you don\u0027t always get a rebuild in, e.g., the CQ. That\u0027s why you need revbumps, etc. But you do get a rebuild when you specifically point emerge at something and don\u0027t use flags like --usepkg.)\n\n[1] Or really, any ebuild, if you\u0027re modifying the non-masked one (which you really shouldn\u0027t do -- you should always modify the 9999 one).",
